<span style="font-family: Arial;"></span>The Constraints and Machine
Learning research group at the Laboratoire LIFO
(<a class="moz-txt-link-freetext" href="http://www.univ-orleans.fr/lifo/">http://www.univ-orleans.fr/lifo/</a>) is seeking post doctoral candidates
with background in <b>Text Mining and Knowledge Discovery</b> for a
one year appointment starting at the latest in January 2011.<br>
<br>
<u><b>The research project</b></u><br>
<br>
The post doctoral position will take place in a bilateral research
project with the university of Beira Interior (Portugal). The project
concerns the development of new approaches to build a prototype-based
ontology from the observation of co-occurrences of terms inside a
corpus. We use the formalism of Pretopology to model the degree of
generality/specificity as well as the semantic closeness between terms
based on asymmetric similarities.<br>
<br>
<br>
<u><b>The prospective candidates must</b></u><br>
<ul>
  <li>have a PhD in Computer Science</li>
  <li>not have the French citizenship</li>
  <li>have knowledge in the theoretical and practical aspects of one or
more of the following:</li>
</ul>
<ul>
  <ul>
    <li>Knowledge discovery from texts</li>
    <li>Information Retrieval</li>
    <li>Clustering and categorization</li>
    <li>Graph models for data analysis</li>
  </ul>
</ul>
<ul>
  <li>have well-developed social skills directed to work in a team</li>
  <li>have a good command of English<br>
  </li>
</ul>
<br>
<u><b>The position offers</b></u><br>
<ul>
  <li>a full time appointment for a period of 12 months</li>
  <li>about 1,900 euros net monthly salary</li>
  <li>attractive and good working environments<br>
  </li>
</ul>
